{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"HTML Entities","slug":"html-entities","subject":"HTML","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"10 minutes","prerequisites":["HTML Text Formatting"],"learning_objectives":["Understand reserved characters","Use entities to display special characters (<, >, &)","Learn common entities (&nbsp; &copy;)"],"theory":"# HTML Entities\n\nSome characters are **reserved** in HTML.\n\nFor example, you cannot use the less than (`<`) or greater than (`>`) signs in your text, because the browser might mix them up with tags.\n\nTo display a reserved character, you must use an **HTML Entity**.\n\n## Syntax\n`&entity_name;` OR `&#entity_number;`\n\n## Common Entities\n\n| Character | Description | Entity Name | Entity Number |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `<` | Less than | `&lt;` | `&#60;` |\n| `>` | Greater than | `&gt;` | `&#62;` |\n| `&` | Ampersand | `&amp;` | `&#38;` |\n| `\"` | Double Quote | `&quot;` | `&#34;` |\n| `'` | Single Quote | `&apos;` | `&#39;` |\n| ` ` | Non-breaking Space | `&nbsp;` | `&#160;` |\n| `©` | Copyright | `&copy;` | `&#169;` |\n\n## Non-Breaking Space (`&nbsp;`)\nA common use is to prevent words from being separated by a line break, or to force multiple spaces (since browsers collapse regular spaces).","syntax":"&entityname;","examples":[{"code":"<p>I love HTML &amp; CSS.</p>\n<p>5 &lt; 10 is true.</p>\n<p>Copyright &copy; 2024</p>","output":"I love HTML & CSS.\n5 < 10 is true.\nCopyright © 2024","explanation":"If we wrote '5 < 10', browser might think < starts a tag."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Forgetting the semicolon","correction":"Entities must end with a semicolon.","example":"❌ &nbsp\n✅ &nbsp;"},{"mistake":"Using entities for all characters","correction":"Only use entities for reserved or invisible characters. Standard letters don't need entities.","example":"Don't write &A; for A."}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"How do you display a < character in HTML text?","difficulty":"Easy","answer":"Use the entity &lt;"},{"question":"What is &nbsp; used for?","difficulty":"Easy","answer":"It stands for Non-Breaking Space. It inserts a space that will not break into a new line. Also used to add multiple visible spaces since browsers collapse normal whitespace."}],"practice_problems":[{"difficulty":"Beginner","problem":"Write a paragraph displaying the code snippet: <h1>Hello</h1>","hint":"Replace brackets with entities.","solution":"<p>&lt;h1&gt;Hello&lt;/h1&gt;</p>"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Displaying Currency","description":"Using entities ensures symbols like Euro (€), Yen (¥), or Cent (¢) display correctly across all encoding systems.","code":"&euro; &yen; &cent;"}],"exam_notes":["Begin with &, End with ;","&lt; for <","&gt; for >","&amp; for &","&nbsp; for extra space","&copy; for copyright"],"summary":"HTML Entities are used to display reserved characters (like < and >) that would otherwise be interpreted as code. They are also used for invisible characters like non-breaking spaces and special symbols like copyright.","order":36},"courseTutorials":[{"slug":"html-document-structure","path":"content/html/html-document-structure.json","title":"HTML Document Structure","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":2},{"slug":"html-comments","path":"content/html/html-comments.json","title":"HTML Comments","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":3},{"slug":"html-editors","path":"content/html/html-editors.json","title":"HTML Editors & Tools","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":4},{"slug":"html-elements","path":"content/html/html-elements.json","title":"HTML Elements","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":5},{"slug":"html-attributes","path":"content/html/html-attributes.json","title":"HTML Attributes","category":"Web Development","subject":"HTML","description":"","order":6},{"slug":"html-audio-video","path